      • isByteArraySame

        public static boolean isByteArraySame​(byte[] bin1,
                                      byte[] bin2)
        Compares if the contents of two byte array are the same.

        When either bin1 or bin2 is null, false will be returned. When either bin1 or bin2 is empty, false will be returned.

        Parameters:
        bin1 - The first byte array
        bin2 - The second byte array
        Returns:
        true if the content are the same, else false
